HEADWORD: Radiate-veined
<hw>Ra"di*ate-veined`</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"d⟦icr⟧*⟦asl⟧t-v⟦amac⟧nd`)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the principal veins
radiating, or diverging, from the apex of the petiole; -- said of such
leaves as those of the grapevine, most maples, and the castor-oil
plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Radiatiform</ent>⟦br⟧
